   <head>To the Reader.</head>
   <p>
      <seg rend="decorInit">I</seg>T is a common custome, to in<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>treat fauour from courteous Rea<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>ders. If the matter bee good, or the men courte<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>ous, the suite of fauour will bee easily granted: if otherwise, it is but a needlesse shame, to beg a commendation, where
<pb facs="3"/>
none is deserued. And therefore I leaue to eue<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>ry man the libertie of his iudgement, and doe expose this Tract to ge<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>nerall censure.</p>
   <closer>
      <signed>F.R.</signed>
   </closer>
</div>
